Senior Policy Adviser Stephen Miller appeared on several news shows to discuss the Trump administration's actions and policies. He emphasized that they are taking every possible action to keep the country safe from terrorism, including pursuing legal avenues to reinstate the travel ban. Miller argued that the President has the authority to conduct immigration and national security policy, and that his powers are beyond question. He also stated that the administration is sending a message of strength and solidarity to the world, particularly in dealing with North Korea's missile test. Miller expressed the belief that American workers should be given jobs first, and that the President is taking forceful action to deliver on his campaign promises.